# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## Project Overview

**Cuaderno de Aula Digital** — a local dashboard application for a vocational training (FP) teacher in the Canary Islands to digitalize the classroom notebook. The primary module is **Sistemas Informáticos** in the **DAW** (Desarrollo de Aplicaciones Web) cycle, academic year 25-26.

## Stack

| Layer     | Technology                                        |
|-----------|---------------------------------------------------|
| Desktop   | Electron 31 + electron-vite                       |
| Main      | Node.js + TypeScript — servicios, SQLite, IPC     |
| Renderer  | Lit Web Components + TypeScript + CSS puro        |
| Base de datos | SQLite via `better-sqlite3`                   |
| Deploy    | Local (localhost), single usuario                 |
| Docs      | VitePress + Mermaid (en `docs/`)                  |

## Data Sources

| Source        | Data                                      | Status            |
|---------------|-------------------------------------------|-------------------|
| Campus/Moodle | Tasks, quizzes, grades, student lists     | API functional    |
| PincelEkade   | Official student roster (matriculation)   | No known API yet  |
| BOE           | Learning outcomes (RA), content, criteria | Public API        |

## Moodle API

- **Base URL:** `https://www3.gobiernodecanarias.org/medusa/eforma/campus`
- **Version:** Moodle 4.5.5+
- **Auth:** CAS SSO — token generated from user profile → Security → Access keys
- **Credentials:** stored in `contextoInicial.txt` (token + userid)

### Relevant web service functions

```
core_enrol_get_users_courses      → teacher's courses
core_enrol_get_enrolled_users     → students per course
mod_assign_get_assignments        → assignments
mod_assign_get_grades             → assignment grades
mod_quiz_get_quizzes_by_courses   → objective tests / quizzes
gradereport_user_get_grade_items  → full gradebook
core_calendar_get_calendar_events → calendar events
core_course_get_contents          → course contents
```

REST endpoint pattern:
```
GET {BASE_URL}/webservice/rest/server.php
  ?wstoken=<token>
  &wsfunction=<function>
  &moodlewsrestformat=json
  &<function-specific-params>
```

